Present law (R.S. 18:1314) provides that the parish board of election supervisors shall meet
at 10:00 a.m. on the fifth day before a primary election and at 10:00 a.m. on the fifth day
before a general election to select parish board commissioners necessary to count absentee
and early voting ballots. Proposed law removes the requirement that the parish board meet
